  ],
};

const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: [
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Do anxiety gummies actually work?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Anxiety gummies containing clinically studied ingredients at therapeutic doses can reduce anxiety symptoms. KSM-66 ashwagandha reduced perceived stress by 30% and cortisol by 11-32% in a 2022 systematic review of 12 RCTs. L-theanine promotes alpha brain wave activity within 30-40 minutes, producing calm alertness. Magnesium glycinate supports GABA activity and nervous system regulation. GABA supplements may reduce anxiety markers within 60 minutes. These ingredients work through different neurological pathways and can be used individually or in combination. However, supplements are not a substitute for therapy or prescribed medication in moderate to severe anxiety disorders.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What is the best ingredient for anxiety relief in gummies?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'For chronic anxiety with elevated cortisol, KSM-66 ashwagandha has the strongest clinical evidence across multiple RCTs. For acute situational anxiety (before presentations, flights, or stressful events), L-theanine works fastest at 30-40 minutes. For anxiety related to magnesium deficiency (affecting 50% of Americans), magnesium glycinate addresses the root cause. GABA provides rapid but shorter-duration calming effects. The most effective approach combines an adaptogen (ashwagandha) for long-term cortisol regulation with an acute agent (L-theanine) for immediate relief when needed.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Are anxiety gummies safe to take with prescription medication?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Anxiety gummies can interact with prescription medications. Ashwagandha may amplify the effects of sedatives, benzodiazepines, thyroid medications, and immunosuppressants. L-theanine may enhance the effects of blood pressure medications. Magnesium can reduce absorption of antibiotics and bisphosphonates. GABA may interact with anti-seizure medications. If you take any prescription medication for anxiety, depression, thyroid conditions, or blood pressure, consult your physician before adding a supplement. Never stop or reduce prescribed medication in favor of supplements without medical guidance.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How quickly do anxiety gummies work?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'L-theanine produces measurable alpha brain wave changes within 30-40 minutes. GABA-based gummies may take 30-60 minutes for noticeable calming. Magnesium glycinate provides acute relaxation effects within 1-2 hours. Ashwagandha requires 2-4 weeks of daily use before cortisol levels begin to decrease measurably, with full anxiolytic effects at 8-12 weeks. For immediate anxiety relief, choose L-theanine or GABA-based products. For long-term anxiety management, ashwagandha-based products are more effective but require patience and consistent daily use.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Can I take anxiety gummies every day?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'L-theanine and magnesium are safe for daily long-term use. Ashwagandha should be cycled — most practitioners recommend 8-12 weeks on followed by 2-4 weeks off — to prevent potential thyroid stimulation with continuous use. GABA supplements are generally safe for daily use but long-term data is limited. Always follow manufacturer dosing recommendations and consult your healthcare provider for personalized guidance on daily supplementation duration, particularly if you have thyroid conditions or take prescription medications.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Do anxiety gummies cause drowsiness?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Properly formulated anxiety gummies should not cause drowsiness when taken at recommended doses. L-theanine promotes relaxed alertness rather than sedation. Ashwagandha reduces cortisol without impairing cognitive function. Magnesium at standard doses has a mild relaxing effect but should not induce sleepiness. However, if a product contains melatonin, valerian root, or high-dose GABA, drowsiness is possible. Check the ingredient list carefully — products labeled for "calm" or "stress" should not contain sleep-inducing ingredients if intended for daytime use.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What is the difference between anxiety gummies and sleep gummies?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Anxiety gummies contain adaptogens (ashwagandha), amino acids (L-theanine, GABA), and minerals (magnesium) that reduce stress without causing drowsiness. They are designed for daytime use. Sleep gummies contain melatonin and sedative herbs (valerian, passionflower) that actively induce sleepiness. Taking a sleep gummy during the day impairs alertness. Taking an anxiety gummy at night may not provide sufficient sedation for insomnia. Choose based on when you need support — daytime stress management (anxiety gummies) or nighttime sleep onset (sleep gummies).' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Are anxiety gummies a substitute for therapy?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'No. Anxiety gummies address the physiological components of anxiety (elevated cortisol, HPA axis dysregulation, neurotransmitter imbalance) but do not address the cognitive and behavioral patterns that maintain anxiety disorders. Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) is the gold standard treatment for anxiety disorders, with meta-analyses showing 50-80% response rates. Supplements are best used as a complementary tool alongside therapy, lifestyle changes (exercise, sleep hygiene, stress management), and when appropriate, prescription medication. If anxiety significantly impairs your daily functioning, seek professional evaluation.' },
    },
  ],
};
