    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Gummies for Anxiety</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do anxiety gummies actually work?</summary>
      <p>Yes, when they contain clinically studied ingredients at therapeutic doses. KSM-66 ashwagandha reduced perceived stress by 30% in a 2022 review of 12 RCTs. L-theanine promotes alpha brain waves in 30-40 minutes. Magnesium supports GABA activity. These are complementary tools, not substitutes for therapy or prescribed medication in moderate to severe cases.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the best ingredient for anxiety?</summary>
      <p>For chronic anxiety: KSM-66 ashwagandha (cortisol reduction over 8-12 weeks). For acute situational anxiety: L-theanine (calm alertness in 30-40 minutes). For deficiency-related anxiety: magnesium glycinate (addresses root cause in 50% of Americans). The best approach combines multiple pathways.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are anxiety gummies safe with prescription medication?</summary>
      <p>Anxiety gummies can interact with sedatives, benzodiazepines, thyroid medications, and blood pressure medications. Always consult your physician before combining supplements with prescribed anxiety or depression medication. Never stop prescribed medication in favor of supplements without medical guidance.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How quickly do anxiety gummies work?</summary>
      <p>L-theanine: 30-40 minutes. GABA: 30-60 minutes. Magnesium: 1-2 hours. Ashwagandha: 2-4 weeks for initial effects, 8-12 weeks for full benefit. Choose L-theanine or GABA for immediate relief, ashwagandha for long-term management.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can I take anxiety gummies every day?</summary>
      <p>L-theanine and magnesium are safe for daily long-term use. Ashwagandha should be cycled (8-12 weeks on, 2-4 weeks off) to prevent thyroid stimulation. GABA is generally safe daily but long-term data is limited. Follow manufacturer dosing and consult your healthcare provider.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do anxiety gummies cause drowsiness?</summary>
      <p>Properly formulated anxiety gummies should not cause drowsiness. L-theanine promotes alert calm, ashwagandha reduces cortisol without sedation. Check labels for hidden melatonin or valerian, which do cause drowsiness. Products in this guide are designed for daytime use.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the difference between anxiety and sleep gummies?</summary>
      <p>Anxiety gummies contain adaptogens and amino acids for daytime stress relief without drowsiness. Sleep gummies contain melatonin and sedative herbs for nighttime sleep onset. Using the wrong type at the wrong time impairs function (sleep gummies during the day) or provides insufficient support (anxiety gummies for insomnia).</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are anxiety gummies a substitute for therapy?</summary>
      <p>No. Supplements address physiological anxiety drivers (cortisol, neurotransmitters, mineral deficiency) but not cognitive-behavioral patterns. CBT has 50-80% response rates for anxiety disorders. Use supplements as complementary support alongside professional care when anxiety significantly impairs daily functioning.</p>
    </details>

